The paper deals with image-based plant localization using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) categories. The use of convolutional neural networks for pose regression and landmark localization also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of global navigation satellite systems, which could indicate a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) in terms of location-based data.
